seafile-server (13.0.25-1~alpha6) unstable; urgency=medium

  * add seahub dir to seafile.env
  * rename units to a seafile- prefix (core: seafile, seahub keeps its name), decouple units via Wants (no stop/restart cascade)
  * drop whitenoise, static assets are served by seahub's SERVE_STATIC default
  * mysql-only backend, migrate gates the stack until credentials are configured
  * enable the go fileserver and notification server by default, units gate on their seafile.env toggle
  * drop SERVICE_URL glue (upstream derives it from the environment), fix references stale since the seahub merge
  * pass REMOTE_USER through gunicorn like upstream's generated config
  * workers and threads set in gunicorn.conf like upstream, drop the env hook
  * fix dead documentation references
  * drop the /etc/default layer and env vars nothing reads, migrate scripts own their environment
  * config templates document the full option surface, notification server binds localhost, seahub logs to the journal
  * connection and process limit defaults sized per service, LimitNOFILE only where fd counts scale
  * dh_ucf owns ucf registration and purge, postinst only adds the --three-way pass
  * secrets are set by the admin instead of generated, migrate gates on all of them
  * dpkg removes /etc/seafile on purge itself, the generated postrm suffices
  * neutral "Other options" section naming in the config templates
  * seafile.conf notes which file server reads single-implementation options
  * unit comments stay service-agnostic so the units diff cleanly
  * seaf-fuse mounts at its state directory, fuse options are a unit directive
  * data dir configured once in seafile.env, fixed unit paths use specifiers
  * version stamp lives in the data dir like upstream docker deployments
  * seahub predefined environment as a section in seafile.env

 -- dionysius <dragon.dionysius@gmail.com>  Wed, 22 Jul 2026 21:33:27 +0200

